               <head>Extracts on Afghanistan</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>Miscellaneous extracts and tracts in Persian relating to the history of
                     Afghanistan, also covering Baluchistan, parts of which are attibuted to the
                     scribes, Yaḥyá Munshī and Ḥusayn ʻAlī.</summary>
                  <msItem
                     class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85064939 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85001521 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85011394 http://lccn.loc.gov/n86066493"
                     n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3770-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Contents include: <list rend="bulleted">
                              <item>March from Kandahar to Qalat <q>Huseer</q> by Yaḥyā [<persName
                                    role="aut">Mīrzā Yaḥyā Munshī</persName>]</item>
                           <item>Baloch tribes of Quetta, by <persName role="aut" key="person_f5692">ʻĀshiq
                                    ʻAlī</persName></item>
                              <item>Memoir on Baluchistan given to Anderson by Major Luck [<persName
                                 role="fmo" key="person_f8604">General Sir George Luck</persName>, G.C.B.,
                                 Colonel of the 15th Hussars], written by one of his employees </item>
                              <item>Account of the fort of Khilat, by Yaḥyā</item>
                              <item>Baloch tribes, by Yaḥyā </item>
                              <item>Account of the Ghilzay tribes, provided by Major Luck </item>
                           <item>Notes on various tribes by <persName role="aut" key="person_f8605">Valī
                                    Muḥammad</persName>
                              </item>
                              <item>Route from Kandahar towards Dera Ismail Khan by <persName
                                 role="aut" key="person_f8606">Amīr Allāh Shāh</persName> given to Anderson
                                 by Major Luck </item>
                              <item>Leading men of Herat and Kandahar by Hasan Ali [ie <persName
                                    role="aut" key="person_f7308">Mīrzā Ḥusayn ʿAlī Khān Hiravī ibn
                                    Rajab ʿAlī Khān</persName>] </item>
                              <item>Rare treatise with graphic diagrams (ff. 228v-242v) on coins
                                 excavated from Kandahar, entitled <title>Z̤arb al-buldān</title>
                                 and composed by Mīrzā Ḥusayn ʿAlī Hiravī for <q>Andarsan Ṣāḥib</q>, the master of Shāh
                                 Shujāʿ al-Mulk's cannonade (<hi rend="italic">tūp khānah</hi>). Prefixed
                                 with a note in English (f. 228r): <q>Transcripts of a few coins
                                    found at Kundahar copied by Husun Alee, 1841</q>. </item>
                           </list>
                        </p>
                        <p></p>
                        <p>IOL stamp: 19 Mar 1909 </p>
                     </note>
